Q. Do you know the lad at the bar? - A. I know him by sight. I never was in company with him before that night;
Richard Thompson
's boy, and another, came down to our house for a Christ mas-box, with the prisoner and his brother, and they said they were going to the play.



      George
       Spurbeck




